At midnight, I stood outside the Federal Reserve’s shadow. A figure melted from the alley—Vito, tossing me a crowbar.  

“You sure?” he asked.  

The lighter flared in my hand. *Rosa* glowed like a beacon.  

“They shouldn’t have used her name.”  

